</rdf:Description>

<rdf:Description rdf:about="https://earth.esa.int/concept/8e8b5e64-af0a-4ef9-805e-0bee03619af4">
	<skos:prefLabel>MEO</skos:prefLabel>
	<skos:definition>Medium earth orbit refers to a specific region in space situated between Low Earth Orbit (LEO) and Geostationary Orbit (GEO). MEO satellites occupy an altitude range typically between 2,000 to 36,000 kilometres (1,243 to 22,300 miles) above the Earth's surface.</skos:definition>
</rdf:Description>

